Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 04-06-17.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years, to run concurrent with 14 CF 161.  One (1) year initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Sex offender treatment and follow through; 
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
3) No contact with any victims;
4) Other than work related or family members, no contact with anyone under age 18; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
6) AODA assessment and follow through counseling.  
Defendant is entitled to 408 days sentence credit.  
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program nor the Substance Abuse Program.   
Minutes.

Bail Jumping - Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Sex offender treatment and follow through;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) No contact with any victims;
4) Other than work related or family members, no contact with anyone under age 18;
5) Pay costs of action;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
8) Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
4th Degree Sexual Assault - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for six (6) months, under the Huber Law, concurrent with jail condition of probation in 14 CF 161.  Defendant is given credit for 118 days time already served.  
$280.00 court costs imposed.  
